						               													<description>Life of Farming is a game where you build your farm from the ground over three years.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It's an exciting game where you will have to make ends meet with your farming operation, and find out whether you have earned a profit by the end of the year. You might even perhaps be crowned farmer of the year.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It won&amp;rsquo;t be a joyride, as the turnable 2-wheeled tractor might make or break your fate and have an impact on your fortune and the weather throughout the year.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Will your harvest come to a standstill due to bad weather, or will your bull win a prize for best bull at the show, all this while struggling to keep track of fields, crops, animals, machinery and helpers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You probably shouldn&amp;rsquo;t trust your neighbors. They might not be as friendly as they look. Will they prevent you from getting any more fields, or hinder you from growing corn? They might however also lend you a tractor because your own is in the workshop, the choices may not always be so true, but they are wise.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It&amp;rsquo;s always a good idea to keep a good relation with the trading stations, as they can supply you with important crops or animals and the machines needed for your farming operation when your money is limited. It is important that you are smart and run your farm with hard work to achieve your goals.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
